==English==

===Verb (intransitive)===
'''stand up'''

# To [[rise]] from a lying or sitting position.
#: ''Stand up, then sit down again.''
#{{cricket}} (''of a wicket-keeper'') to stand immediately behind the wicket so as to catch balls from a [[slow bowler|slow]] or [[spin bowler]], and to attempt to [[stump]] the batsman

====Translations====

*Esperanto: [[starigu]]
*French: [[se lever]] 
*Interlingua: [[leva te]] 
*Italian: [[leva in piedi]] 
*Portuguese: [[levantar-se]] 
*Romanian: [[ridica]]
*Spanish: [[levantarse]]

===Verb (transitive)===
'''stand up'''

# To bring something up and set it into a standing position.
#: ''Laura stood the sofa up on end''
#{{idiom}} To avoid a prearranged meeting with someone; to [[jilt]] or [[shirk]].
#: ''John stood Laura up at the movie theater''

